Description: DuckBotOS OpenClaw agent mode — verified secondary agent
 Installs OpenClaw as the primary desktop agent for DuckBotOS.
 OpenClaw boots as a fullscreen agent interface, providing a verified
 secondary agent that can spawn sub-agents, manage memory, and coordinate
 with Hermes via the agent bus.
 .
 Ports:
   18797 — Chat agent (main agent interface)
   18794 — ACP protocol server (agent-to-agent communication)
   18796 — WebSocket streaming (real-time streaming responses)
   3850  — MCP protocol bridge (tool exposure to external systems)
   4000  — Agent mesh networking (peer discovery + broadcast)
   4001  — Sub-conscious memory daemon (LLM-powered long-term memory)
 .
 Sub-agents: sessions_spawn with MiniMax, Grok, or LM Studio backends.
 MCP tools: 64+ DuckBot Brain memory tools, desktop control, shell exec.
 GDM session "DuckBotOS OpenClaw" boots directly to OpenClaw dashboard.
 .
 Compatible with Hermes for dual-agent hybrid mode (P4).
 Agent mesh allows spawning sub-agents across multiple machines.
